Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Trim the
@carrots{3}(trimmed and halved lengthways), then halve lengthways (no need to
peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Peel the @garlic cloves{2}
but leave them whole.

Pour the boiling water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.5%tsp}.

Add the potatoes and garlic cloves to the water and cook until you can easily
slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Cumberland sausages{8} and carrots onto a large
#baking tray{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Season the carrots with @salt{}
and @black pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the carrots are tender and
the sausages are browned and cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}. Turn halfway
through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw sausages. They're
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%grams}(halved lengthways).

When about ~{10%minutes} of roasting time remain, add the Tenderstem® to
another baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, season, then toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use another tray if necessary.

Roast on the middle shelf for the remaining time until the broccoli is tender
and crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}.

If you'd prefer to, boil your broccoli in step 4 while the jus cooks, until
just tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain and return to the pan. Drizzle
with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

While everything roasts, pour the @water for the jus{150%milliliter} into a
small #saucepan{} and bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{15%grams}, then reduce the heat to medium-high.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water
> for 1 min.

Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed, then remove from
the heat and cover with a #lid{} or #foil{} to keep warm.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan,
off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{1%splash}
(if you have any), then mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Cover with a lid to keep
warm.

Share the garlic mash between your plates.

Top with the sausages, then pour over the red wine jus (reheat first if needed).

Serve the roasted carrots and Tenderstem® broccoli alongside. Enjoy!